00:35:02.208 --> 00:35:03.728
high-resolution reconstructed

593
00:35:04.828 --> 00:35:08.408
duct in this case. All right, so CODA is a 3D mapping

594
00:35:08.508 --> 00:35:12.088
technique that is agnostic for organs, for species.

595
00:35:12.408 --> 00:35:14.388
We've done many different type of species.

596
00:35:14.648 --> 00:35:18.448
Disease, I've shown you, of course, quite of work on

597
00:35:18.508 --> 00:35:21.548
cancer, but we've looked at autoimmune disease, we've looked at

598
00:35:22.828 --> 00:35:26.288
psoriasis in particular, and can be integrated with

599
00:35:26.588 --> 00:35:29.468
multiplex IF, multiplex Codex, et cetera.

600
00:35:30.228 --> 00:35:33.328
I'm going to stop here and recognize my

601
00:35:33.788 --> 00:35:37.328
wonderful colleagues, in particular Laura Wood and Ralph Huber,

602
00:35:37.968 --> 00:35:41.768
Ashley Kimiec now is independent, and Peishan Wu, partner in crime

603
00:35:42.128 --> 00:35:42.468
in this

604
00:35:43.328 --> 00:35:45.128
development of CODA and its validations.

605
00:35:52.268 --> 00:35:56.128
Thank you very much, Dennis. So like I said, we're going to leave the questions

606
00:35:56.148 --> 00:35:56.608
till the end.

